<item>
            <title>[CXF-5504] AbstractLoggingInterceptor.getMessageLogger throws NPE when MultipleEndpointObserver is used</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-5504</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The method &lt;tt&gt;AbstractLoggingInterceptor#getMessageLogger(Message)&lt;/tt&gt; that was introduced by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-3888&quot; title=&quot;Logging interceptors: Create a separate logger category for each service so they can be configured indepenently&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CXF-3888&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CXF-3888&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; assumes that &lt;tt&gt;message.getExchange().getEndpoint()&lt;/tt&gt; is not null.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This assumption does not work if one uses &lt;tt&gt;org.apache.cxf.transport.MultipleEndpointObserver&lt;/tt&gt; as the message observer, leading to NPE:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;java.lang.NullPointerException: null
	at org.apache.cxf.interceptor.AbstractLoggingInterceptor.getMessageLogger(AbstractLoggingInterceptor.java:78) ~[cxf-2.5.9.jar:2.5.9]
	at org.apache.cxf.interceptor.LoggingInInterceptor.handleMessage(LoggingInInterceptor.java:73) ~[cxf-2.5.9.jar:2.5.9]
	at org.apache.cxf.phase.PhaseInterceptorChain.doIntercept(PhaseInterceptorChain.java:263) ~[cxf-2.5.9.jar:2.5.9]
	at org.apache.cxf.transport.MultipleEndpointObserver.onMessage(MultipleEndpointObserver.java:98) [cxf-2.5.9.jar:2.5.9]
...
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Would it be possible to check first if endpoint is present?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
